# TDD Agent - CatchFire Matching Engine

## Full Testing Picture

This project has **three layers** of testing. All three are important.

### Layer 1: Automated Unit Tests (vitest)

Catches regressions in schemas and scoring logic. Runs in CI and locally.

- **Framework:** Vitest 3.x
- **Config:** `vitest.config.ts`
- **Test Location:** `tests/*.test.ts`
- **Run Tests:** `npm test` (vitest run) or `npm run test:watch` (vitest)
- **Module System:** TypeScript source (compiled to CommonJS)

| File | Tests | Coverage |
|------|-------|----------|
| `tests/schemas.test.ts` | 38 tests: Zod schemas, validation helpers, constants | `src/schemas.ts` |
| `tests/scoring.test.ts` | 41 tests: Scoring algorithm, keyword extraction, ranking | `src/scoring.ts` |

### Layer 2: Stakeholder / Manual QA Testing

For Dan and stakeholders to evaluate match quality and API behavior hands-on.

| Resource | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `docs/TESTING_FOR_STAKEHOLDERS.md` | Step-by-step guide: how to run the server, test endpoints, curl examples for POST /match |
| `docs/TESTING_AND_DEPLOY_PLAN.md` | Deploy plan, feedback loop (thumbs up/down to Google Sheets), pre-Dan checklist |

### Layer 3: Browser-Based Testing UI

A working temp UI for match-by-brief and per-result feedback, served by the engine itself.

| Resource | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `public/testing.html` | Served at `/testing` -- paste brief, see ranked creators, give thumbs up/down per result |
| Feedback endpoint | `POST /api/v1/feedback` -- sends ratings to Google Sheet when `FEEDBACK_SHEET_ID` is set |

**How they fit together:** Unit tests (Layer 1) ensure code correctness before deploy. The testing UI (Layer 3) and stakeholder docs (Layer 2) let Dan and the team evaluate match quality and provide feedback that drives iteration.

